Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight Glimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.20,0:00:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure I saw her, Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.18,0:00:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home, Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.48,0:00:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We travelled back in time to\Nwhen Rainbow Dash performed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.68,0:00:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,her first Sonic Rainboom?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the Rainboom,\Nyou and your friends
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.78,0:00:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will never form your\Nspecial cutie mark bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.36,0:00:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever Starlight did in\Nthe past changed things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.88,0:00:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to live in\Nthat awful future we saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.78,0:00:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think\Nyou'll have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.46,0:00:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All servants of Queen\NChrysalis found in these woods
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.52,0:00:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,must be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.28,0:00:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hearing impaired subtitles\Nby YayPonies\NWe have muffins!\Nhttp://yayponies.eu/
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.46,0:01:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! We're not changelings!\NI'm a pony! And he's a dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A likely story!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.18,0:01:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do something dragonish!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.12,0:01:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That works.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.39,0:01:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The servants of Chrysalis\Nwill do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.48,0:01:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to save their evil skins!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.94,0:01:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,STOP!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.36,0:01:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If they are\Nchangelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.64,0:01:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll soon see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.86,0:01:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I think they're not\Nwhat they appear to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.56,0:01:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Zecora! Please,\Nyou have to listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.46,0:01:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Beneath this salve\Nno changeling hides,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.82,0:01:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for it reveals the\Ntruth inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.80,0:02:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.18,0:02:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The meaning is far worse, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.96,0:02:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For it is we who should not be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.26,0:02:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.13,0:02:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you can, but\Nlet's not talk here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chrysalis and her army\Nwill soon draw near.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The changelings took\Nover not long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.98,0:02:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,though I'll wager in\Nyour world that isn't so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.58,0:02:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Chrysalis and her army tried\Nto take over Canterlot,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but my friends\Nand I stopped her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.29,0:02:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Those friends as you know\Nthem are not here, alas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.76,0:02:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But tell me how all\Nthis came to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.29,0:02:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight Glimmer. A pony\Nwho traveled back in time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.42,0:02:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop my friends and me\Nfrom ever coming together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.28,0:02:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is these friends\Nyou have in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.60,0:02:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that keep Equestria\Nfree from strife?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so. But this is the\Nsecond time I've come back
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.96,0:03:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and this world is even\Nworse than the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.56,0:03:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If Starlight keeps doing\Nthe same thing in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.32,0:03:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,how could the present\Nbe so different?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahhh, time is a river where even\Nthe tiniest changes seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.14,0:03:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Can lead to a cascade\Nof effects downstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.08,0:03:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This part of the forest\Nis dark and damp,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.66,0:03:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's done well\Nto hide our camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.58,0:03:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is cozy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.12,0:03:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, you have to help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.62,0:03:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The changelings\Nattacked Ponyville.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We barely escaped\Nwith our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The only changeling\Nattack I see
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is the one that come\Nhere looking for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.68,0:03:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's taken quite a while\Nto find you, Zecora.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What a lovely\Nvillage you've chosen
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.74,0:04:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to stage your little resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.28,0:04:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks absolutely\Ndelicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.18,0:04:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come now, Zecora,\Nyou're vastly outnumbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.44,0:04:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you don't want\Nyour charges hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.06,0:04:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Come quietly to the\Ndungeons of Canterlot
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.98,0:04:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I promise to leave\Nthe others alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.92,0:04:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would she ever trust you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.24,0:04:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if there's a chance\NChrysalis will honor her word,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.70,0:04:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't you try?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Race to the map while we\Nhold off their attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop Starlight and put the\Nwhole world back on track.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.46,0:05:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to make a decision, Zecora.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.42,0:05:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if what you are\Nsaying were true,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.44,0:05:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd never surrender\Nto a creature like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad. But it's going to\Ntake a lot more than that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.26,0:05:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky for you, there's\Nmore where that came from!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.32,0:05:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You've really got\Nto work on your aim!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,WHOA!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.24,0:06:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? You\Nhave to finish your race!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.86,0:06:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! This is\Nway more exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.18,0:06:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See? You can't stop me\Nno matter what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.56,0:06:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you obviously\Ndon't mean us failing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's becoming\Npretty routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.52,0:06:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's just the other\Ntimes we've come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.74,0:06:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's been day, but look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would the map\Nwould bring us back
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.00,0:06:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to a different time of\Nday than when we left?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.38,0:06:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, maybe we should\Nfigure it out later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.04,0:07:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Castle of the Two Sisters!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.36,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't just stand here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.14,0:07:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This place looks a lot\Ncleaner than I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.66,0:07:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarity?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The castle isn't open\Nfor viewings today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.42,0:07:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The tapestries all need\Nchanging... again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.34,0:07:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarity, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.26,0:07:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't socialize with dragons.\NI don't know anypony who would.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.52,0:07:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarity, you have\Nto listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The future of\NEquestria is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.24,0:07:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how\Nyou know my name,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.40,0:08:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but I am far too busy to\Nentertain some tourist's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.70,0:08:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,ridiculous fantasies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.46,0:08:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to get back to the\Nmap so I can stop Starlight
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.95,0:08:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from changing the past because\Nevery present I come to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is worse than the last!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Time travel, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.22,0:08:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's something\NI would like to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.06,0:08:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me how you came by this\Nmagic to travel through time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.68,0:08:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Princess asked\Nyou a question!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless you want to\Nend up in the dungeon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.56,0:08:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll tell her what\Nshe wants to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.58,0:08:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No pony in my kingdom but\Nme should possess a magic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.70,0:08:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful enough to change time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.10,0:08:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Your kingdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.22,0:08:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Who else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:08:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Celestia, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.56,0:09:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister has been imprisoned\Nin the moon for years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.82,0:09:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is no less a fate\Nthan she sentenced me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.82,0:09:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now. Reveal to me the\Nsource of this time magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.32,0:09:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.82,0:09:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no choice, Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take you to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.78,0:09:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but you'll have to get\Npast the Timber Wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.24,0:09:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the ruler of\Nall of Equestria.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.46,0:09:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I can't\Ndeal with Timber Wolves?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.24,0:09:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I know you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.08,0:09:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you were thinking\Nof trying to escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.70,0:09:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be very\Nunfortunate for your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.46,0:09:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.88,0:10:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A pony from my time used a spell
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.80,0:10:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to travel back and\Nchange the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.18,0:10:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you will give\Nthis spell to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.22,0:10:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,With it, I will ensure that\Nthe Elements of Harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.02,0:10:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,are never found and\Nmy rein lasts forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.88,0:10:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But it won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.24,0:10:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.24,0:10:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In my world, my friends\Nand I found the elements
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and used them to defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.20,0:10:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will do\Neverything in my power
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.96,0:10:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring that world back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.16,0:10:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,NOOOOOOO!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.54,0:10:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now more than ever, I know how\Nimportant it is to stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.94,0:10:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.38,0:10:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.72,0:11:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Up for another race-ending\Nfight, Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No. You were right.\NI can't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't stop\Nme from trying
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.46,0:11:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we could be stuck doing\Nthis for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.50,0:11:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's what it takes to\Nkeep you and your friends
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.96,0:11:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,from getting your cutie mark\Nconnection, then I'm game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.36,0:11:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're doing goes\Nway beyond cutie marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.34,0:11:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything we do\Nhere in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.41,0:11:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,even the smallest change,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,can snowball into an avalanche\Nof trouble for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Next I suppose\Nyou'll tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that the fate of\Nall of Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.19,0:12:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hangs in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.02,0:12:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,IT DOES!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Spare me your over-blown ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.66,0:12:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No group of friends, not\Neven Princess Twilight's,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.47,0:12:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is that important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how important\Nother ponies' friendships are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.74,0:12:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can show you what the\Nworld is like without mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.42,0:12:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.04,0:12:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The future. Or\Nrather, the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.78,0:12:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.78,0:12:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could say\NI was surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.98,0:12:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But every world I come back\Nto is worse than the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.32,0:12:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why my friends\Nand I are so important
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to Equestria, but we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.72,0:13:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.66,0:13:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Starlight. Look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.38,0:13:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, everything in\Nthe past affects the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.90,0:13:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,even the tiniest act, and\Nwhat you're doing leads here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.78,0:13:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I can't stop you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.54,0:13:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but I thought showing you\Nthis might change your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.33,0:13:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Change my mind? You don't\Nknow anything about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was perfectly happy\Nbefore you and your friends
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,ruined what I built.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.86,0:13:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened\Nthat led you to make
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your village\Nwithout cutie marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.70,0:13:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sorry my friends\Nand I had to take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.30,0:13:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know what happened\Nto me? I'll show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.26,0:13:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That map of yours is connected\Nto every part of Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.48,0:13:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and this part is my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.00,0:14:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunburst and I did\Neverything together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I don't remember\Nus ever being apart...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.88,0:14:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,until today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.61,0:14:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And just like that,\Nmy friend was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.70,0:14:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,His family recognized\Nhis magical talent
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.10,0:14:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and sent him off to Canterlot.\NI never saw him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.56,0:14:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.78,0:14:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of his cutie mark!\NHe got his and I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.23,0:14:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He moved on and I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.56,0:15:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I stayed here and never\Nmade another friend
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.96,0:15:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was too afraid\Nanother cutie mark
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.27,0:15:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,would take them away too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.40,0:15:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.68,0:15:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A cutie mark can't\Ntake your friends away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.31,0:15:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everypony's lucky\Nenough to get her cutie mark
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.70,0:15:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time as her friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.38,0:15:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what it's\Nlike to lose a friend
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.74,0:15:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because of a cutie mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But once I stop the\NRainboom, you will!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I destroy this scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.70,0:15:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,there'll be no way\Nfor you to change it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.78,0:15:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.47,0:15:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what\Nyou went through,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.37,0:15:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but I do know you\Ncan't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen where this\Nleads and so have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.68,0:15:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I only saw what\Nyou showed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.60,0:15:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what'll\Nreally happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.16,0:15:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen it a dozen times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.90,0:15:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Things don't turn out\Nwell in an Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.52,0:15:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,without my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.94,0:16:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh! What's so special\Nabout your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.08,0:16:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How can a group of ponies\Nthat are so different
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.80,0:16:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,be so important?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.18,0:16:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The differences between\Nme and my friends
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.92,0:16:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are the very things that\Nmake our friendship strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.10,0:16:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought Sunburst\Nand I were the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.44,0:16:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but we turned out different
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.92,0:16:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and it tore our\Nfriendship apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So try again. Make new friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.44,0:16:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And if something that\Nyou can't control happens
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.26,0:16:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that changes things, work\Nthrough it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.12,0:16:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what friendship is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.45,0:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not just my\Nfriendships that are important
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to Equestria. Everyponies' are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When yours ended,\Nit led us here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.56,0:16:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but just imagine all the\Nothers that are out there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.58,0:16:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting for you if you\Njust give them a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.26,0:16:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I know they won't\Nall end the same way?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.10,0:16:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's up to you\Nto make sure they don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.96,0:17:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One Castle of\NFriendship. Check.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.74,0:17:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What in Equestria was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everypony OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.92,0:17:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.31,0:17:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One group of amazing\Nfriends. Check.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Spike. It looks\Nlike we're home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, what's she doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.76,0:17:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's kind\Nof a long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I knew my\NRainboom was awesome,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.66,0:17:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but I never thought all of\NEquestria depended on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.64,0:17:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Or on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.22,0:17:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.80,0:18:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Friendship connects\Nall of Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.96,0:18:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and undoing one group\Nof friends
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.54,0:18:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,made its magic\Nless powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.54,0:18:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe y'all\Nwere able to travel
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.38,0:18:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,through time like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That Starlight must\Nbe pretty magical!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.65,0:18:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She obviously has\Nmore talent for magic
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.76,0:18:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,than almost any pony I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.96,0:18:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My magic couldn't stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.74,0:18:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to convince her\Nto stop on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.14,0:18:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I realized that,\Neverything fell into place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.53,0:18:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But if she's as\Npowerful as all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.70,0:18:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we can't just send her\Non her way, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.98,0:18:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I kind of have\Nsomething else in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.52,0:18:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I know there's no\Nexcuse for what I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but I want you all to\Nknow that I'm ready
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.80,0:18:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for whatever punishment\Nyou think is fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.46,0:18:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking a lot about\Nhow badly Equestria fared
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,without just one\Ngroup of friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.00,0:18:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because even when\None friendship dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.06,0:18:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the results can\Nbe disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.66,0:19:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, firsthoof,\Nhow true that can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I've\Nasked you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.74,0:19:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're willing\Nto learn,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.40,0:19:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm willing to teach\Nyou what I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have the power\Nto make Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.34,0:19:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an even better place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.90,0:19:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I start?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.30,0:19:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting is easy. All you\Nhave to do is make a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.82,0:19:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've got seven\Nof them right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.50,0:19:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ I never thought that I{\i0}\N{\i1} would find a place, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.22,0:19:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ to step right in{\i0}\N{\i1} and start again ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.12,0:19:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ I never thought that{\i0}\N{\i1} I could just begin, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.42,0:19:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Right where I left{\i0}\N{\i1} off and make a friend. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.82,0:19:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Don't ever think that{\i0}\N{\i1} it might be too late. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.56,0:19:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ You don't have to wait, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.88,0:20:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ there's no mistakes with{\i0}\N{\i1} the friends you make. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ A friendship's only{\i0}\N{\i1} made of what you bring, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.27,0:20:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ and if you do it right,{\i0}\N{\i1} you can do anything. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.68,0:20:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Just use... your eyes...{\i0}\N{\i1} this time... no lies ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.48,0:20:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Just don't... disguise...{\i0}\N{\i1} who you are inside. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.68,0:20:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Because your friends are{\i0}\N{\i1} always there for you. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.80,0:20:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ You don't have to{\i0}\N{\i1} be the same ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.53,0:20:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ For friendship to be true. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.30,0:20:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Because your friends are{\i0}\N{\i1} always there for you. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Around the world{\i0}\N{\i1} it's still the same, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.28,0:20:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ together you have{\i0}\N{\i1} more to gain. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.01,0:20:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ There's nothing that{\i0}\N{\i1} a friend won't do ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.85,0:20:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Everywhere you go,{\i0}\N{\i1} friendship there will grow ♪{\i0}
